  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Are there any games like Robinson Crusoe?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several board games and video games that share thematic similarities or gameplay elements with *Robinson Crusoe: Adventures on the Cursed Island*, a cooperative board game where players work together to survive on a deserted island. Here are some games that might appeal to fans of *Robinson Crusoe*:\n\n### **Board Games:**\n1. **Forbidden Island / Forbidden Desert:**  \n   Cooperative games where players work together to survive and escape from a dangerous island or desert. Both games emphasize teamwork and resource management.\n\n2. **Dead of Winter:**  \n   A cooperative (with potential traitor) survival game set in a post-apocalyptic world. Players must manage resources, fend off zombies, and complete objectives.\n\n3. **Pandemic:**  \n   While not survival-themed, it\u2019s a cooperative game where players work together to stop the spread of diseases. It shares the teamwork and strategic planning aspects of *Robinson Crusoe*.\n\n4. **The 7th Continent:**  \n   A cooperative exploration and survival game where players are stranded on a mysterious island and must solve puzzles and survive the environment.\n\n5. **Spirit Island:**  \n   A cooperative game where players take on the roles of spirits defending their island from colonizers. It involves strategy, resource management, and teamwork.\n\n6. **Survive: Escape from Atlantis!**  \n   A semi-cooperative game where players try to escape a sinking island while avoiding sea creatures and helping their own survivors escape.\n\n### **Video Games:**\n1. **The Forest:**  \n   A survival horror game where players must gather resources, build shelter, and fend off cannibalistic mutants on a remote island.\n\n2. **Stranded Deep:**  \n   A survival game where players are stranded in the Pacific Ocean and must explore islands, gather resources, and build tools to survive.\n\n3. **Don\u2019t Starve / Don\u2019t Starve Together:**  \n   A survival game with a dark, whimsical art style. Players must gather resources, craft tools, and manage hunger and sanity while exploring a mysterious world.\n\n4. **Subnautica:**  \n   A survival game set on an alien ocean planet. Players must gather resources, build underwater bases, and explore the depths to survive and escape.\n\n5. **Green Hell:**  \n   A survival game set in the Amazon rainforest. Players must manage hunger, hydration, and health while dealing with the dangers of the jungle.\n\n6. **Raft:**  \n   A survival game where players start on a small raft and must gather debris from the ocean to expand their raft and survive shark attacks.\n\n### **Tabletop RPGs:**\n1. **Tales from the Loop / Things from the Flood:**  \n   While not strictly survival games, these RPGs focus on storytelling and exploration in a mysterious, often perilous environment.\n\n2. **The Quiet Year:**  \n   A map-drawing RPG where players collaboratively tell the story of a struggling community trying to survive.\n\nIf you enjoy the survival, exploration, and cooperative aspects of *Robinson Crusoe*, these games should provide a similar experience!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
